The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Hyderabad, June 8: The first trial proceeding in the Rs 10,000-crore Satyam scam began in a local court here today. The economic offences court, which took up one of the cases filed by the Serious Fraud Investigation Office against Satyam founder B. Ramalinga Raju and other former directors of Satyam, posted the case to July 2 for further hearing.                             
	 New Delhi, June 8: Government revenue from 3G and broadband wireless auction (BWA) spectrum sale crossed Rs 1 lakh crore today, the 13th day of the auction, with BWA bids for the Tamil Nadu and Punjab circles exceeding the 3G bids. The pan-India BWA licence touched Rs 11,518 crore at the end of 102 rounds of auction.                             
	 New Delhi, June 8: An expert panel headed by HDFC chief Deepak Parekh has asked the government to change rules to allow funding by pension and insurance companies. The panel recommended that a debt fund of Rs 50,000 crore be set up for financing infrastructure projects.                             
	 Kuala Lumpur, June 8: The International Air Transport Association expects airlines to post a global profit of $2.5 billion this year compared with the previous forecast of $2.8-billion loss released in March .                            
	 Chennai, June 8: Hyundai Motor India today said the strike in its Sriperumbudur plant near Chennai continued and it would seek the state governments help to resolve the issue even as a conciliatory meeting between the management and the union remained inconclusive.                             
	 New Delhi, June 8: Ranbaxy Laboratories has launched the generic version of cholesterol lowering drug atorvastatin in South Africa under the brand Lipogen.                             
	 Mumbai, June 8: O.P. Bhatt, chairman of the State Bank of India, has been elected new chairman of the Indian Banks Association (IBA) for 2010-11.
                                                                                                                          
